The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Teams fined
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Teams fined
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Jaipur: The Indian Premier League (IPL) on Friday announced that it had fined the Deccan Chargers and Kings XI Punjab $ 1,000 for slow over rate for the match played in Hyderabad on Thursday.         
	The chairman amp; commissioner of the IPL, Lalit Modi announced that any team bowling a slow over rate would be fined $500 per over, and the decision would be taken by the match referee.                                                                                                                          
